info.name: Aragon Backend
info.description: The Aragon API is a service within the Aragon backend, designed to expose indexed data from the Aragon DAOs ecosystem on the Aragon OSx protocol through a REST API.

item.name: Aragon Networks
item.description:
The Aragon Backend-API supports all networks where the Aragon protocol is deployed, ensuring comprehensive access to the Aragon DAOs ecosystem.

**Aragon Networks**

Ethereum Mainnet = _**ethereum-mainnet**_

Polygon Mainnet = _**polygon-mainnet**_

Base Mainnet = _**base-mainnet**_

Arbitrum Mainnet = _**arbitrum-mainnet**_

ZkSync Era Mainnet = _**zksync-mainnet**_

Ethereum Sepolia = **ethereum-sepolia**

ZkSync Era Sepolia = **zksync-sepolia**

item.name: Aragon DAO ID
item.description: Aragon assigns a unique ID to each DAO for easier data retrieval and management. This DAO ID follows the format `{aragonNetwork}-{daoAddress}`, where `aragonNetwork` is the network on which the DAO is deployed, and `daoAddress` is the unique address of the DAO.

item.name: Supported DAOs
item.description:
The Aragon API supports all DAOs that adhere to the standards of the Aragon OSx protocol. This ensures comprehensive access to DAOs that are fully integrated within the Aragon ecosystem.

DAOs that do not conform to these standards may not be displayed or accessible through the API. By maintaining this standard, the Aragon API guarantees a consistent and reliable experience for developers and users interacting with compliant DAOs on the platform.
